<h2>Why HVAC Companies Wrap Their Fleets</h2>

<p class="body-text">HVAC service vehicles are uniquely positioned for maximum advertising impact. Unlike most commercial vehicles, HVAC vans are parked in residential driveways for hours during installations and service calls. Every neighbor walking their dog, every mail carrier, every parent driving past sees your brand — building familiarity and trust that translates directly into phone calls when their furnace goes out or their AC stops working.</p>

<p class="body-text">Chicago's extreme seasons drive year-round demand for HVAC services. A wrapped van in a suburban neighborhood during a January cold snap or July heat wave becomes the most trusted name on the block. Homeowners don't search Google when their furnace fails at 2 AM — they call the company they've seen in their neighborhood. At $0.04–$0.07 per thousand impressions, fleet wraps cost a fraction of Google Ads, mailers, or Angi leads — with zero recurring cost.</p>

<p class="body-text">The ROI math is clear: a single HVAC van wrap costing $3,500 generates an estimated 16+ million impressions over its 5-year lifespan. Compare that to digital advertising at $3.56 CPM — the equivalent ad spend would be $57,000+. Fleet wraps are the single most cost-effective marketing investment available to HVAC companies in the Chicago market.</p>
